</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p "> Check the function of the ink level low sensor of the ink tank. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the sensor assembly from the ink tank to test the correct working of the sensor ( see 
<xref keyref="02DISA001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-3C378CEF-8BD5-4962-B1D3-3085A8622216.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 How to remove the ink low sensor (02B1/3/5/7)?>02 How to remove the ink low sensor (02B1/3/5/7)</xref> up to step 4, do not disconnect the harness).
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Start the test. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The sensor can be activated by touching the sensor area with your hand.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The level sensor has two diagnostic LED’s:
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Green LED: power supply indicator, led is activated when +24V power is present. Should be ON.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Yellow LED: function indicator, indicates the detection of ink/no-ink.
</p></li></ul><table id="GUID-70F143AC-7884-4D15-ACD7-FFEE16456747" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor status 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Low level sensor 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Yellow LED 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor output level 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">no ink detected 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">ON 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">+24 V 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink detected 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">OFF 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">0 V 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><note id="GUID-4B449C0F-2B75-4D73-8649-E874DAD6407C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The orange led of the HIGH level sensor has a different behavior (inverted)
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-92369981-F020-4E62-9707-58F93D054214" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Values</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Active (1) = Ink is detected (Yellow LED is off). Refill not allowed. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In Inactive (0) = No ink is detected (Yellow LED is on). Refill allowed.
</p></li></ul></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-E4C54F6E-7FBD-467E-A9DF-8C20AA8FEAEE.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
